 <td colspan = "5" background = "bckground.gif" bgcolor = "#FFFFFF">

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<div class="indented">
<p>Q - <u>How do I create an account?</u><BR>
A - On the Bubooks.com homepage, simply look for the link that says "Sign UP!," and follow the instructions.<BR></p>
<p>Q - <u>Do I have to be a member to search for a book?  </u><BR>
A - You must be a member to get the seller's information after searching.  This is only to maintain the privacy of our users.  Creating an account takes only about thirty seconds. <BR></p>
<p>Q - <u>Why can't I log in?</u><BR>
A - Bubooks.com requires cookies be enabled in your browser for session management.<BR></p>
<p>Q - <u>How do I add a book to the Bubooks.com database?</u><BR>
A - First, sign in at the Bubooks.com homepage. From there you will be brought to your personal homepage where there is a link to add your books.  <BR></p>
<p>Q - <u>How do I change my account information if I move?</u><BR>
A - After signing in, there is a link in the top left of your homepage that says "Update/ Change My account information." Simply click on the link and fill in the info.<BR></p>
<p>Q - <u>Am I responsible for deleting my sold books?</u><BR>
A - YES!  If you don't you will continue getting inquiries about the book after you have sold it.<BR></p>
<p>Q - <u>How do I delete a book?</u><BR>
A - First, sign in to your account. "Select" the box next to the textbook which you like to delete.  Then look at the lower left hand corner of the book table and press the "Delete Selected" button.<BR></p>
<p>Q - <u>How do I search for a book other than by TITLE?</u><BR>
A - On the search engine next to title there is a downward facing arrow.  Press on it to get the options of ISBN, Author, or Course.<BR></p>
<p>Q - <u>What is an ISBN number?</u><BR>
A - An ISBN is a 10 digit number printed on the back of ALL Textbooks.  Searching by ISBN is the fastest and most reliable way to search because every edition of a book has its own ISBN.<BR></p>

<h2>Profrate</h2>

<p>Q - <u>How do I rate a professor?</u><BR>
A - At ProfRate, take a look at the list of all the professors already listed.  If your professor is listed, click on his/her name then click on the link saying Add a Rating.  If your Professor is not on the list, click on the link Create a New Professor Rating Entry and post!<BR></p>
<p>Q - <u>What does Narrow By Department do?</u><BR>
A - Narrowing by department will show ONLY the professors listed in the specific field chosen. <BR></p>
<p>Q - <u>How do I add a rating to an existing professor?</u><BR>
A - Go to the professor's rating page and look for the flashing link that says "Add a rating".  Click on this.  <BR></p>
<p>Q - <u>What do I do if I feel a particular professor rating is inappropriate?</u><br>
A - Next to each rating there is a "File Complaint" button.  Click that and give us a short reason why the comment is offending. We will do our best to remove the rating as fast as possible.<br></p>
<p>Q - <u>What makes a rating inappropriate?</u><br>
A - A rating which uses profanity, defamatory, infringing, obscene, or dishonest information 
would be considered inappropriate.<br></p>
<p>Q - <u>What is Bubooks.com looking for in a Professor rating?</u><br>
A - A appropriate rating would consist of specific reasons why you like or dislike a professor's style of teaching, what class you took with the prof, your grade, if there was HW or Quizzes, how much studying you had to do, if you recommend the class or not, ect.....
</div><br>



